Set oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source and preheat the oven's broiler. Place artichoke hearts in a bowl; mash with a fork. Stir in olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Cut baguette into 8 slices, about 1/2-inch thick; place slices on baking sheet. Broil both sides until toasted, 3 to 5 minutes. Slice garlic clove in half; rub on one side of each slice. Top bread slices with artichoke spread.